            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EJesus%20taught%20us%20that%20the%20ultimate%20act%20of%20love%20is%20to%20lay%20down%20our%20lives%20for%20others.%20In%20fact%2C%20Jesus%20stated%2C%20%22The%20Father%20loves%20me%20because%20I%20lay%20down%20my%20life%20that%20I%20may%20have%20it%20back%20again%22%20(John%2010%3A17).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPeople%20who%20consider%20the%20needs%20of%20others%20ahead%20of%20their%20own%20are%20true%20shepherds%20in%20the%20spirit%20of%20Jesus.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20people%20with%20hireling%20spirits%20are%20concerned%20only%20for%20what%20relates%20to%20their%20own%20well-being.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPaul%20said%2C%20%22I%20have%20no%20one%20else%20like%20Timothy%2C%20who%20genuinely%20cares%20about%20your%20welfare%22%20(Philippians%202%3A20).%20The%20true%20love%20of%20Christ%20is%20defined%20in%201%20John%203%3A16%3A%20%22We%20know%20what%20real%20love%20is%20because%20Christ%20gave%20up%20his%20life%20for%20us.%20And%20so%20we%20also%20ought%20to%20give%20up%20our%20lives%20for%20our%20Christian%20brothers%20and%20sisters.%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJust%20as%20David%20abandoned%20his%20own%20safety%20and%20went%20to%20rescue%20Keilah%20(1%20Samuel%2023%3A2)%2C%20we%20must%20abandon%20our%20own%20self-interests%20and%20begin%20to%20lay%20down%20our%20lives%20for%20others.%20We%20will%20not%20lose%20our%20lives%3B%20we%20will%20take%20them%20up%20again!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "1Sam.22:1-23:29",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Samuel%2022%3A1-23%3A29%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_1%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Samuel%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%20at%20the%20Cave%20of%20Adullam%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20David%20left%20Gath%20and%20escaped%20to%20the%20cave%20of%20Adullam.%20Soon%20his%20brothers%20and%20all%20his%20other%20relatives%20joined%20him%20there.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_2%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20others%20began%20coming%26%23x2014%3Bmen%20who%20were%20in%20trouble%20or%20in%20debt%20or%20who%20were%20just%20discontented%26%23x2014%3Buntil%20David%20was%20the%20captain%20of%20about%20400%26%23xA0%3Bmen.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_3%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3ELater%20David%20went%20to%20Mizpeh%20in%20Moab%2C%20where%20he%20asked%20the%20king%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BPlease%20allow%20my%20father%20and%20mother%20to%20live%20here%20with%20you%20until%20I%20know%20what%20God%20is%20going%20to%20do%20for%20me.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_4%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20parents%20stayed%20in%20Moab%20with%20the%20king%20during%20the%20entire%20time%20David%20was%20living%20in%20his%20stronghold.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_5%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20day%20the%20prophet%20Gad%20told%20David%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BLeave%20the%20stronghold%20and%20return%20to%20the%20land%20of%20Judah.%26%23x201D%3B%20So%20David%20went%20to%20the%20forest%20of%20Hereth.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_6%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20news%20of%20his%20arrival%20in%20Judah%20soon%20reached%20Saul.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20the%20king%20was%20sitting%20beneath%20the%20tamarisk%20tree%20on%20the%20hill%20at%20Gibeah%2C%20holding%20his%20spear%20and%20surrounded%20by%20his%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_7%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BListen%20here%2C%20you%20men%20of%20Benjamin!%26%23x201D%3B%20Saul%20shouted%20to%20his%20officers%20when%20he%20heard%20the%20news.%20%26%23x201C%3BHas%20that%20son%20of%20Jesse%20promised%20every%20one%20of%20you%20fields%20and%20vineyards%3F%20Has%20he%20promised%20to%20make%20you%20all%20generals%20and%20captains%20in%20his%20army%3F%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E22%3A7%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ecommanders%20of%20thousands%20and%20commanders%20of%20hundreds%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_8%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EIs%20that%20why%20you%20have%20conspired%20against%20me%3F%20For%20not%20one%20of%20you%20told%20me%20when%20my%20own%20son%20made%20a%20solemn%20pact%20with%20the%20son%20of%20Jesse.%20You%26%23x2019%3Bre%20not%20even%20sorry%20for%20me.%20Think%20of%20it!%20My%20own%20son%26%23x2014%3Bencouraging%20him%20to%20kill%20me%2C%20as%20he%20is%20trying%20to%20do%20this%20very%20day!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_9%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Doeg%20the%20Edomite%2C%20who%20was%20standing%20there%20with%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20men%2C%20spoke%20up.%20%26%23x201C%3BWhen%20I%20was%20at%20Nob%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20saw%20the%20son%20of%20Jesse%20talking%20to%20the%20priest%2C%20Ahimelech%20son%20of%20Ahitub.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_10%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EAhimelech%20consulted%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20for%20him.%20Then%20he%20gave%20him%20food%20and%20the%20sword%20of%20Goliath%20the%20Philistine.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_11%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Slaughter%20of%20the%20Priests%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EKing%20Saul%20immediately%20sent%20for%20Ahimelech%20and%20all%20his%20family%2C%20who%20served%20as%20priests%20at%20Nob.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_12%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20they%20arrived%2C%20Saul%20shouted%20at%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BListen%20to%20me%2C%20you%20son%20of%20Ahitub!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20is%20it%2C%20my%20king%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20Ahimelech%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_13%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20have%20you%20and%20the%20son%20of%20Jesse%20conspired%20against%20me%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20Saul%20demanded.%20%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20did%20you%20give%20him%20food%20and%20a%20sword%3F%20Why%20have%20you%20consulted%20God%20for%20him%3F%20Why%20have%20you%20encouraged%20him%20to%20kill%20me%2C%20as%20he%20is%20trying%20to%20do%20this%20very%20day%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_14%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BBut%20sir%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20Ahimelech%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3Bis%20anyone%20among%20all%20your%20servants%20as%20faithful%20as%20David%2C%20your%20son-in-law%3F%20Why%2C%20he%20is%20the%20captain%20of%20your%20bodyguard%20and%20a%20highly%20honored%20member%20of%20your%20household!%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_15%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20was%20certainly%20not%20the%20first%20time%20I%20had%20consulted%20God%20for%20him!%20May%20the%20king%20not%20accuse%20me%20and%20my%20family%20in%20this%20matter%2C%20for%20I%20knew%20nothing%20at%20all%20of%20any%20plot%20against%20you.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_16%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BYou%20will%20surely%20die%2C%20Ahimelech%2C%20along%20with%20your%20entire%20family!%26%23x201D%3B%20the%20king%20shouted.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_17%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20he%20ordered%20his%20bodyguards%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BKill%20these%20priests%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20for%20they%20are%20allies%20and%20conspirators%20with%20David!%20They%20knew%20he%20was%20running%20away%20from%20me%2C%20but%20they%20didn%26%23x2019%3Bt%20tell%20me!%26%23x201D%3B%20But%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20men%20refused%20to%20kill%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20priests.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_18%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20king%20said%20to%20Doeg%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20do%20it.%26%23x201D%3B%20So%20Doeg%20the%20Edomite%20turned%20on%20them%20and%20killed%20them%20that%20day%2C%20eighty-five%20priests%20in%20all%2C%20still%20wearing%20their%20priestly%20garments.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_19%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20went%20to%20Nob%2C%20the%20town%20of%20the%20priests%2C%20and%20killed%20the%20priests%26%23x2019%3B%20families%26%23x2014%3Bmen%20and%20women%2C%20children%20and%20babies%26%23x2014%3Band%20all%20the%20cattle%2C%20donkeys%2C%20sheep%2C%20and%20goats.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_20%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EOnly%20Abiathar%2C%20one%20of%20the%20sons%20of%20Ahimelech%2C%20escaped%20and%20fled%20to%20David.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_21%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20he%20told%20David%20that%20Saul%20had%20killed%20the%20priests%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_22%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20exclaimed%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20knew%20it!%20When%20I%20saw%20Doeg%20the%20Edomite%20there%20that%20day%2C%20I%20knew%20he%20was%20sure%20to%20tell%20Saul.%20Now%20I%20have%20caused%20the%20death%20of%20all%20your%20father%26%23x2019%3Bs%20family.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_22_23%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EStay%20here%20with%20me%2C%20and%20don%26%23x2019%3Bt%20be%20afraid.%20I%20will%20protect%20you%20with%20my%20own%20life%2C%20for%20the%20same%20person%20wants%20to%20kill%20us%20both.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_23_1%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Samuel%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%20Protects%20the%20Town%20of%20Keilah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20day%20news%20came%20to%20David%20that%20the%20Philistines%20were%20at%20Keilah%20stealing%20grain%20from%20the%20threshing%20floors.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_23_2%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20asked%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BShould%20I%20go%20and%20attack%20them%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BYes%2C%20go%20and%20save%20Keilah%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20told%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_23_3%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20men%20said%2C%20%26%23